<img class="img-responsive" src="sites/all/themes/hpcl_ret/images/reminero_bottle1.png" alt="Reminero Bottle" style="float:right; padding: 16px 0px 16px 16px;"/>
<p>HPCL has forayed into a new product line of Re-Mineralised Nano-Filtered Packaged Drinking Water under Brand 'REMINERO' in Collaboration with the CSIR-Indian Institute of Chemical Technology (CSIR-IICT), Hyderabad.</p>
<p>The CSIR-Indian Institute of Chemical Technology (CSIR-IICT), Hyderabad is a premier R & D Institute, which was established way back in 1944. CSIR-IICT carries out research in chemical sciences leading to innovative processes for a variety of products necessary for human welfare such as food, health, energy and environment. CSIR-IICT has made its mark as a dynamic, innovative and result oriented R & D organization. CSIR — IICT is already in collaboration with HPCL’s Green R & D Centre for developing various collaborative projects.</p>
<p>HPCL has entered into an agreement with CISR-IICT with an objective to seek. their expertise in ‘membrane technology’ along with infra-structure support for manufacturing Re-Mineralised Nano-Filtered Packaged Drinking Water adhering to the prevailing standards. This initiative, besides being a value added service to the customers visiting our Retail outlets would make available packaged drinking water fortified with minerals to the public at large.</p>
<p>A modern plant is commissioned at CSIR-IICT; Hyderabad campus with latest technology for manufacturing of packaged drinking water and licenced by BIS & FSSAI.</p>
